    <p><span><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>Dose of an antibiotic is 100 mg, how many doses are there in 10 g of antibiotic.</p>
    <div class="formulae"><p>$$ No. of Doses = {10000 \ mg \over 100 \ mg}$$</p></div>
    <p><span><strong>Answer: </strong></span>100 doses</p>
    
    </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
                                <td>
    <p><span><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>If 100 ml of a cough syrup contains 20 doses, how many teaspoonfuls are there in each dose?</p>
    <div class="formulae"><p>$$ 20 = {100 \ ml \over size \ of \ dose}$$</p></div>
    
    <div class="formulae"> <p>$$ size \ of \ dose = 5 \ ml = 1 \ teaspoon $$</p></div>
    
    <p><span><strong>Answer: </strong></span>1 teaspoon</p>
    
    </td>
    </tr>
    
